{"title_page": "CIX (band)", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = CIX\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = 190724 CIX Debut Showcase (cropped).png\n| landscape        = yes\n| alt              = \n| caption          = CIX in their debut showcase on July 2019.<br />From left to right: Hyunsuk, BX, Jinyoung, Yonghee, and Seunghun\n| alias            = \n| origin           = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[PBR&B]]|[[hip hop]]}}\n| years_active     = {{Start date|2019}}\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[C9 Entertainment|C9]]|[[Warner Music Japan|Warner Japan]]}}\n| website          = [http://c9ent.co.kr/?c=artist&s=1&artist_id=89 Official web]<br/>[https://cix-official.jp/ Japan official web]\n| current_members  =\n* BX\n* Seunghun\n* Yonghee\n* [[Bae Jin-young]]\n* Hyunsuk\n}}\n\n'''CIX''' ({{lang-ko|\uc528\uc544\uc774\uc5d1\uc2a4|Ssi-a-i-ekseu}}, pronounced as C-I-X, short for '''Complete in X''') is a five member South Korean boy group formed by [[C9 Entertainment]] in 2019, consisting of BX, Seunghun, Yonghee, [[Bae Jin-young]] and Hyunsuk.\n\nThe group debuted on July 23, 2019, with their first [[extended play|EP]] titled ''[[Hello Chapter 1: Hello, Stranger]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/109/0004043780|title='\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601 \uadf8\ub8f9' CIX, \ub370\ubdd4 \uc1fc\ucf00\uc774\uc2a4 \ud2f0\ucf13 \uc624\ud508 \ub3d9\uc2dc\uc5d0 \ub9e4\uc9c4..\ub300\uae30\uc790\ub3c4 5\ucc9c\uba85 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Pre-debut===\n[[Bae Jin-young]] competed in Mnet's ''[[Produce 101 Season 2]]'' in April 2017 representing C9 Entertainment, soon finishing in 10th place and joining project boy group [[Wanna One]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://star.mbn.co.kr/view.php?year=2017&no=488956&refer=portal|title=\ube0c\ub79c\ub274\ubba4\uc9c1 \uce21 \u201c\u2018\ud504\ub4c02\u2019 \uc774\ub300\ud718\u00b7\ubc15\uc6b0\uc9c4\u00b7\uc784\uc601\ubbfc\u00b7\uae40\ub3d9\ud604, \uc804\uc18d\uacc4\uc57d \uccb4\uacb0 \uc644\ub8cc\u201d(\uacf5\uc2dd) - \uc5f4\ub9b0\uc138\uc0c1 \uc5f4\ub9b0\ubc29\uc1a1 MBN|website=star.mbn.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> In October 2017, Lee Byoung-gon appeared as a contestant on JTBC's ''[[Mix Nine]]'', finishing in 9th place thus earning a spot in the winning group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003774151|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5 \uc804\ubb38] YG\uce21 \"'\ubbf9\uc2a4\ub098\uc778' \ub370\ubdd4 \ubb34\uc0b0, 6\uacf3 \uae30\ud68d\uc0ac\uc640 \ud611\uc758 \ub05d \uacb0\uc815..\uc8c4\uc1a1\"|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> However, YG later decided not to debut said group.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=109&aid=0003774151|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5 \uc804\ubb38] YG\uce21 \"'\ubbf9\uc2a4\ub098\uc778' \ub370\ubdd4 \ubb34\uc0b0, 6\uacf3 \uae30\ud68d\uc0ac\uc640 \ud611\uc758 \ub05d \uacb0\uc815..\uc8c4\uc1a1\"|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> As both Lee and fellow bandmate Kim Seung-hun were [[YG Entertainment|YGE]] trainees, in 2018 the two competed in the survival show ''YG Treasure Box'' for the label's next boy group, [[Treasure 13]] where both failed to debut in the finale.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.topstarnews.net/news/articleView.html?idxno=627473|title=\uc774\uc608\uc9c0 \uae30\uc790 - [\uc774\uc288\uc885\ud569] C9BOYZ \uc774\ubcd1\uace4-\uae40\uc2b9\ud6c8-\uae40\uc6a9\ud76c-\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601-\uc724\ud604\uc11d, \uadf8\ub8f9 \uba85 \uc528\uc544\uc774\uc5d1\uc2a4(CIX) \ud655\uc815\u2026\u2018\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ub370\ubdd4 \ubaa9\ud45c\u2019(feat.YG\uc5f0\uc2b5\uc0dd \ucd9c\uc2e02\uba85)|date=May 21, 2019|website=www.topstarnews.net|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> In November 2017, Kim also appeared on Mnet survival program ''[[Stray Kids (TV series)|Stray Kids]]'' while still a YGE trainee.{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\n===2019-2020: Debut and Japanese debut===\nAhead of debut, the group broadcast the reality show ''Hello CIX'' on June 4, 2019 through [[V Live (website)|V Live]]. The show consisted of 10 episodes showcasing the group\u2019s various charms and road to debut.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=410&aid=0000588183|title=\u2018\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601 \uadf8\ub8f9\u2019 CIX, \ub370\ubdd4 \ub9ac\uc5bc\ub9ac\ud2f0 \u2018HELLO CIX\u2019 \ucd9c\uaca9\u20266\uc6d4 4\uc77c \uccab \ubc29\uc1a1|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On July 23, 2019 CIX made their debut with EP ''[[Hello Chapter 1: Hello, Stranger]]'' and lead single \"Movie Star\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/609/0000130042|title=\u2018\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601 \uadf8\ub8f9\u2019 CIX, 7\uc6d423\uc77c 1st \uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4-24\uc77c \uc1fc\ucf00\uc774\uc2a4 \uac1c\ucd5c(\uacf5\uc2dd)|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> The album was a mild commercial success, selling 70,000 copies in two months.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20191119000855|title=CIX goes political in \u201cHello, Strange Place,\u201d raises voice for teenagers|date=November 19, 2019|website=www.koreaherald.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> They held their debut showcase on July 24 at [[SK Olympic Handball Gymnasium]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0001116446|title=\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601 \uadf8\ub8f9 CIX, \ub370\ubdd4 \uc1fc\ucf00\uc774\uc2a4 \ud3ec\uc2a4\ud130 \uacf5\uac1c\u2026\uccad\ub7c9\u7f8e \ubfdc\ubfdc|website=entertain.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On the July 30 episode of ''[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]],'' they beat [[Pentagon (South Korean band)|Pentagon]] and [[VAV (band)|VAV]] to win first place,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/112/0003194356|title=[\uc885\ud569]'\ub354\uc1fc' CIX, \ub370\ubdd4\uc640 \ub3d9\uc2dc\uc5d0 1\uc704 \ub4f1\uadf9\u2026\uacf5\uc6d0\uc18c\ub140\u00b7\ud39c\ud0c0\uace4 \ucef4\ubc31|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> becoming the second fastest group to get their first win, after [[Winner (band)|Winner]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\nOn August 27, C9 Entertainment announced that CIX have signed with Warner Music Japan for Japanese debut.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nid=04&c1=04&c2=04&c3=00&nkey=201908261151023&mode=sub_view|title=\uc138\uacc4\ub85c \ubed7\uc5b4 \uac00\ub294 CIX|website=bntnews.hankyung.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On October 23, they debuted in Japan with a Japanese version of their EP ''Hello Chapter 1: Hello, Stranger'', including the song \"My New World\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://n.news.naver.com/entertain/article/215/0000818200|title=CIX(\uc528\uc544\uc774\uc5d1\uc2a4), 23\uc77c \u65e5 \ud504\ub9ac\ub370\ubdd4 \uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026\ubbf8\ubc1c\ud45c \uc2e0\uace1 \u2018My New World\u2019 \uc218\ub85d|website=n.news.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> On November 10, CIX held their Japanese debut showcase \"Complete In X\" at [[Shibuya Public Hall|Line Cube Shibuya]], and November 17 at [[Zepp Namba]].<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/d_news/detail/80487/2|title=\u97d3\u56fd5\u4eba\u7d44\u30dc\u30fc\u30a4\u30ba\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30fbCIX\u3001\u65e5\u672c\u76e4\u300eHELLO Chapter\u2160. Hello, Stranger\u300fJK\u5199\uff06A\u5199\u516c\u958b {{!}} Daily News|website=www.billboard-japan.com|language=ja|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 19, CIX released their second EP ''[[Hello Chapter 2: Hello, Strange Place]]'' with the lead single \"Numb\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20191101143500005|title=CIX, \ub450 \ubc88\uc9f8 \ubbf8\ub2c8\uc568\ubc94 \ubc1c\ub9e4\u2026'\uc548\ub155, \ub0af\uc120 \uacf5\uac04'|website=www.yna.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn April 1 2020, CIX will debut in the Japanese market with the release of their 1st Single ''Revival''.\n\n==Members==\nAdapted from their Naver profile<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://search.naver.com/search.naver?sm=mtb_pcv&where=nexearch&query=CIX|title=CIX : \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \ud1b5\ud569\uac80\uc0c9|website=search.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref> and website profile.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://c9ent.co.kr/?c=artist&s=1&artist_id=89|title=CIX : C9 ENTERTAINMENT|website=c9ent.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=February 24, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cix-official.jp/|title=CIX Japan Official Website|website=cix-official.jp|language=ja|access-date=November 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n* BX (\ube44\uc5d1\uc2a4) \u2013 leader, main rapper, vocal \n* Seunghun (\uc2b9\ud6c8) \u2013 main vocalist, lead dancer\n* Yonghee (\uc6a9\ud76c) \u2013 vocal, visual\n* [[Bae Jin-young]] (\ubc30\uc9c4\uc601)  \u2013 lead vocalist, lead dancer, center, fotg \n* Hyunsuk (\ud604\uc11d) \u2013 vocal, lead rapper, main dancer, maknae\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of extended plays, with selected chart positions and sales\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:24em;\" | Details\n! colspan=\"3\" | Peak chart positions\n! rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\" | Sales\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Gaon Album Chart|KOR]]<br><ref>Charted EPs on [[Gaon Album Chart]]:\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=30&hitYear=2019&