|list=|league_wins=12|league_losses=14|CEO_title=CEO|league_draws=0|league_champions=|league=NRL|high_attendance=62,255 {{small|(vs. Cronulla, round 1)}}|cup_result=|cup=|coach=[[David Waite]] & [[Andrew Farrar]]|captain2=|captain=[[Nathan Brown (rugby league, born 1973)|Nathan Brown]]|avg_attendance=14,922|assistant_coach=|year=2000}}The '''2000 St. George Illawarra Dragons season''' was the second in the [[St. George Illawarra Dragons|joint venture club]]'s history. The Dragons competed in the [[National Rugby League|NRL]]'s [[2000 NRL season|2000 premiership season.]] The team finished ninth in the regular season, missing out on finals for the first time in their history.\n\n== Squad gains and losses ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:700px;\"\n!{{increase}} or {{decrease}}\n!Player\n!1999 Club\n!2000 Club\n!Source\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Jamie|Fitzgerald|Jamie Fitzgerald (rugby league)}}\n|{{Leagueicon|Norths}} [[North Sydney Bears]]\n|{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]]\n| rowspan=\"12\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rugbyleagueproject.org/teams/st-george-illawarra-dragons/transfers.html|title=St George Illawarra Dragons - Gains & Losses - Rugby League Project|website=www.rugbyleagueproject.org|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Solomon|Haumono}}\n|{{Leagueicon|Balmain}} [[Balmain Tigers]]\n|{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]]\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Lee|Hookey}}\n|{{Leagueicon|Souths}} [[South Sydney Rabbitohs]]\n|{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]]\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Wes|Patten}}\n|{{Leagueicon|Souths}} [[South Sydney Rabbitohs]]\n|{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George Illawarra Dragons]]\n|-\n|{{increase}}\n|{{sortname|Robbie|Simpson|Robbie Simpson (rugby league)}}\n|{{Leagueicon|London}} [[London Broncos]] ([[Super League]])\n|{{Leagueicon|St. George Illawarra}} [[St. George I